      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": null,
      "message": "Same comment but instead of K8s job objects, we already have this baked in for K8s pod status:\n\nCan you check if the python script we already have baked into the readiness image is the same as this?  At first glance it does and this seems redundant unless you are doing something different.\n\nhttps://github.com/onap/oom/tree/master/kubernetes/readiness/docker/init\n\nIf you do need this, I would prefer a fix/flag or new script checked into the path above that is built into the readiness-image.  we could then up-rev that to 2.0.1 and have it one place.  \nI would rather not have python scripts that are fairly generic and kubernetes specific embedded in as configmaps.",
